| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| Language | English |
| Keyboard | Your preference |
| Installation type | Ubuntu Server |
| Network | DHCP (auto) |
| Proxy | Leave blank |
| Mirror | Default |
| Storage | **Use entire NVMe disk only** (don't touch HDDs) |
| LVM | ✅ Keep enabled (default) |
| Your name | Breen |
| Server name | `city17` |
| Username | `breen` |
| Password | Your choice (strong) |
| SSH | ✅ Install OpenSSH server |
| SSH keys | Import from GitHub (enter your GitHub username) |
| Featured Snaps | Skip all |
| Third-party drivers | Accept/Enable |

---

## After Successful Install

1. Reboot, remove USB, disconnect monitor/keyboard
2. From aperture, find city17's IP:
   ```bash
   nmap -sn 192.168.68.0/24
   # or
   ping city17.local
   ```
3. SSH in:
   ```bash
   ssh breen@<city17-ip>
   ```
4. Continue to **Phase 2: Network Setup** (see agents.md)

